node.text:
2020 Elk Season Highlights [30 of 30]:⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Elk Season 2020 will likely go down as one of the tougher elk hunting seasons we can remember. The rut seemed subdued - it seemed to start late and end early. Fires and smoke, extreme heat and dry conditions, and multiple other factors contributed to consistent frustrations. But, in every hardship, there came renewed determination and rewards for persistence.⁠⠀
*⁠⠀
Destination Elk V3 will be kicking off within the pages of the University of Elk Hunting Online Course for all active Members in January, and we'll be bringing the full release to everyone else during the summer months leading up to elk season.⁠⠀
*⁠⠀
We'll be bringing you a total of 9 successful elk hunts - and the lessons learned from several additional unsuccessful days - in the raw style you've become accustomed to. A total of nearly 30 episodes will make up this season's Destination Elk series, and we can't wait to kick it off and share it with you!⁠⠀
*⁠⠀
If you're not already a member of the University of Elk Hunting, you can sign up today using the code DEV3 to save $30! This is our biggest discount of the year, and it's for a very limited time. Sign up today, and be the first to see the entire season of Destination Elk V3, as well as have opportunities to win some awesome gear. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
#universityofelkhunting #destinationelkV3 #elk101 #elkhunting #elkseason⁠⠀

node.text:
Do you like elk hunting? Do you want to hunt elk with Corey Jacobsen during the peak of the rut this fall? Here is your chance!

Elk101 has teamed up with our good friends @mtnops to bring you the #ultimateelkhunt giveaway! One lucky winner is going to be going on an all expense paid 5 day Elk Hunt this fall with Corey Jacobsen!

For all the details, and to get entered, click the link in our bio!

#UltimateElkHunt #elk101 #ElkHunting #Elk #ConquerMore #DestinationElk

node.text:
"I was finally able to take my first bull elk ever and did it on public land in Colorado this year. The University of Elk Hunting Online Course played a big part in my success. Coming from Central Kentucky and only hunting whitetails on “flatland,” I had to prepare myself with as much knowledge as possible in a remote at home situation. The online scouting, calling, training, and game preparation, helped speed this process tremendously. It is definitely worth the money to help prepare you for the hunt."

- James Koontz

Congratulations on a great bull James, and thank you for the kind words! #testimonialthursday #universityofelkhunting #elk101 #elk101success
